# 📄 PRODUCT REQUIREMENTS DOCUMENT (PRD)

## 🧠 Project Title

Relief-Map: Hyper-Local Crowdsourced Aid Hub

---

## 🎯 Product Vision

Develop a real-time, AI-powered, hyper-local emergency and safety platform that connects people in need with nearby helpers (within 2 km radius), supporting both disaster situations and day-to-day safety needs such as women safety, elderly assistance, and medical emergencies.

The system must provide **instant help access (1-click SOS), real-time coordination, AI assistance, and government-level monitoring dashboards**.

---

## 🚨 Problem Statement

In both disasters and everyday emergencies:

* There is no **instant, hyper-local coordination system**
* People nearby are willing to help but cannot discover requests
* Response delays can cost lives
* Vulnerable groups (women, elderly) lack fast-access help tools
* Authorities lack real-time visibility of ground-level situations

---

## 💡 Solution Overview

Build a **single unified platform** with:

* A **shared dashboard for all users**
* A **helper availability toggle system**
* A **1-click SOS emergency system**
* AI-powered assistance and prioritization
* Real-time updates and notifications
* Multilingual accessibility
* A **government/admin monitoring dashboard**

---

# 🔥 CORE PRODUCT FEATURES

---

## 1. 🧑‍🤝‍🧑 Unified Dashboard + Helper Toggle System

* Single dashboard for all users
* Toggle option:
  👉 “Available to Help” (ON/OFF)

### Behavior:

* Users with toggle ON:

  * Receive nearby help notifications
  * Appear as helpers on map
* Users with toggle OFF:

  * Do not receive help notifications
  * Can still request help anytime

---

## 2. 🚨 1-Click SOS Emergency System (CRITICAL FEATURE)

### For users needing immediate help:

* SOS button visible prominently
* On click:

  * Option 1: 🎙️ Record voice message describing situation
  * Option 2: 📋 Quick-select predefined emergency options

### Smart Options:

* Dynamically generated based on:

  * Gender (e.g., women safety options)
  * Situation (disaster vs daily emergency)
  * Location context

Examples:

* “I am in danger”
* “Medical emergency”
* “Need immediate rescue”
* “Unsafe situation”

---

## 3. 🎙️ Voice-to-Text AI Processing

* Recorded voice is:

  * Converted to text (Speech-to-Text)
  * Sent to helpers as readable message
* Helps in:

  * Faster understanding
  * Accessibility

---

## 4. 📍 Geo-Tagged Requests & Offers

Each request includes:

* GPS location
* Category
* Urgency
* Description (text/AI generated)

---

## 5. 📡 Hyper-Local Feed (≤ 2 KM)

* Only show nearby requests
* Use GeoHash-based filtering (Firestore)

---

## 6. ⚡ Real-Time Sync

* New requests appear instantly
* Status updates sync instantly
* Use Firebase real-time listeners

---

## 7. 🗺️ Map-Based System

* Google Maps integration
* Show:

  * 🔴 Requesters
  * 🟢 Helpers (toggle ON users)
* Real-time movement and updates

---

## 8. 💬 Real-Time Chat System

* Communication between helper and requester
* Auto-expire after resolution

---

## 9. 🔔 Smart Notification System

### Trigger notifications:

* New SOS nearby
* New request nearby
* Help accepted
* Status updates

---

## 10. 📊 Status & Flag System (IMPORTANT)

Each request will maintain states:

* 🟡 Requested
* 🔵 Help Accepted
* 🟠 Help On The Way
* 🟢 Help Completed
* 🔴 Emergency Escalated

These flags must update in real-time.

---

## 11. 🌍 Multilingual Support

* App supports multiple regional languages
* Use Google Multilingual APIs

### Features:

* Translate UI dynamically
* Translate requests for helpers
* Voice input in native language

---

## 12. 🤖 AI INTEGRATION (CRITICAL)

### A. AI Chatbot Assistant

* Helps users understand what to do
* Provides guidance in emergencies

---

### B. AI Triage System

* Classifies requests automatically:

  * Category
  * Urgency
* Extracts key info from text/voice

---

### C. AI Priority Ranking

* Rank requests based on:

  * Urgency
  * Distance
  * Time

---

## 13. 📈 Stats & Impact Dashboard

Display:

* Number of people helped
* Active requests
* Completed requests
* Response times

---

## 14. 🛡️ Admin / Government Master Dashboard

### Features:

* Real-time map view of:

  * All requests
  * All helpers
* Heatmaps of crisis zones
* Analytics:

  * High-risk areas
  * Response times
* Useful for:

  * Government
  * NGOs

